#Approach:

Approach (Hinglish):

1. Pehle Floyd Cycle Detection use karte hain:
   - slow 1 step chalega
   - fast 2 step chalega

2. Agar cycle hai, to slow aur fast kisi point par mil jayenge.

3. Jaise hi dono mil jayein:
   - slow ko dobara head par le aao
   - ab slow aur fast dono 1-1 step move karo

4. Jis node par dono dobara milenge,
   wahi cycle ka starting node hoga.

5. Agar fast ya fast.next null ho jaye,
   to cycle exist nahi karti, return null.

Main Idea:
- First meeting point cycle confirm karta hai
- Second meeting point cycle ka start deta hai

Time Complexity: O(N)
Space Complexity: O(1)


#code:

/**
 * Definition for singly-linked list.
 * class ListNode {
 *     int val;
 *     ListNode next;
 *     ListNode(int x) {
 *         val = x;
 *         next = null;
 *     }
 * }
 */
public class Solution {
    public ListNode detectCycle(ListNode head) {

        if(head == null || head.next == null){
            return null;
        }

        ListNode slow = head;
        ListNode fast = head;

        //Detection of a cycle
        while(fast != null && fast.next != null){
            slow = slow.next;
            fast = fast.next.next;

            //if detected then chase down to starting point
            if(slow == fast){
                slow = head;
                while(fast != slow){
                    slow = slow.next;
                    fast = fast.next;
                }
                return slow;
            }
        }
        return null;        
    }
}
